%20population%20regardless%20of%20financial%20status%20to%20support%2C%20but%20not%20replace%2C%20their%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENumerous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foregon-opposition-measure-118-basic-income-corporate-tax-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecities%20and%20counties%20in%20the%20United%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20also%20experimented%20with%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20programs.%20These%20programs%20are%20similar%20to%20a%20UBI%20because%20they%20both%20provide%20no-strings-attached%20payments%2C%20but%20a%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20typically%20goes%20to%20smaller%2C%20low-income%20groups%2C%20or%20vulnerable%20populations%20like%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguaranteed-universal-basic-income-ubi-baltimore-young-families-success-fund-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20moms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorgia-basic-income-program-low-income-black-women-debt-bills-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlack%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudicial-watch-sues-san-francisco-basic-income-program-trans-people-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrans%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20these%20programs%20have%20likened%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Bsocialism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20lawmakers%20in%20South%20Dakota%2C%20Iowa%2C%20and%20Idaho%20passed%20laws%20banning%20basic%20income%20programs%20at%20the%20city%20and%20county%20level.%20Republican%20State%20Sen.%20John%20Wiik%2C%20who%20sponsored%20the%20bill%20in%20South%20Dakota%2C%20said%20in%20a%20Senate%20committee%20meeting%20that%20basic%20income%20programs%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bsocialist%20idea%26quot%3B%20that%20redistributes%20people's%20hard-earned%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGuaranteed%20income%20programs%2C%20also%20known%20as%20basic%20income%2C%20undercut%20the%20dignity%20in%20earning%20a%20dollar%2C%20and%20they're%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20to%20government%20dependency%2C%26quot%3B%20Wiik%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20study%2C%20however%2C%20found%20that%20recipients%20maintained%20steady%20employment%2C%20showed%20improved%20mental%20health%2C%20strengthened%20self-determination%2C%20and%20improved%20financial%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20a%20basic%20income%2C%20people%20actively%20build%20sustainable%20financial%20security%20for%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20spend%20more%20money%20on%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJ%C3%BCrgen%20Schupp%2C%20a%20researcher%20for%20the%20study%2C%20said%20that%20the%20results%2C%20particularly%20those%20related%20to%20labor%2C%20show%20that%20many%20clich%C3%A9s%20about%20universal%20basic%20income%20need%20to%20be%20reconsidered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%20for%20the%20urgently%20needed%20restructuring%20of%20social%20systems%2C%20all%20reform%20options%20must%20be%20considered%20%E2%80%94%20including%20universal%20basic%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-study-germany-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747004068000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6821243ea466d2b74ab5a0ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-study-germany-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20German%20basic%20income%20study%20found%20no%20change%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20hours%20that%20participants%20worked%20a%20week%20over%20three%20years%2C%20despite%20monthly%20payments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A92%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-study-germany-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20founded%20a%20%24100%20million%20home%20decor%20startup%20during%20the%202008%20recession.%20Here's%20my%20advice%20for%20starting%20a%20company%20in%20crisis.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jenny%20Jing%20Zhu%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68193e96a466d2b74ab518d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJenny%20Jing%20Zhu%20came%20to%20the%20US%20as%20a%2026-year-old%20who%20spoke%20little%20English.%20She%20started%20her%20home%20design%20company%20Lush%20Decor%20amid%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis.%3Cp%3EJenny%20Jing%20Zhu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJenny%20Jing%20Zhu%20came%20to%20the%20US%20as%20a%2026-year-old%20who%20spoke%20very%20little%20English.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZhu%20started%20Lush%20Decor%2C%20a%20home%20design%20company%2C%20amid%20the%20economic%20troubles%20of%202008.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20managed%20to%20survive%20the%20downturn%2C%20which%20Zhu%20said%20made%20her%20more%20resilient.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jenny%20Jing%20Zhu%2C%2051%2C%20New%20Jersey-based%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Lush%20Decor%2C%20a%20digital%20home%20decor%20company.%20She%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshould-you-start-a-business-during-recession-general-economic-uncertainty-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Echallenges%20of%20starting%20a%20business%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20in%20an%20uncertain%20time%20and%20how%20she%20overcame%20it.%20BI%20has%20verfied%20her%20company%20information.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20Lush%20Decor%20in%202008%2C%20I%20was%20quietly%20going%20through%20the%20toughest%20time%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ruth-porat-lesson-great-recession-financial-crisis-advice-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20economy%20was%20collapsing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20divorce.%20I%20was%20learning%20how%20to%20be%20a%20parent%20to%20my%20then-1-year-old%20son.%20And%20I%20was%20an%20immigrant%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENew%20York%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estill%20speaking%20broken%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20had%20already%20survived%20a%20lot%20of%20hard%20things%20in%20my%20life%20and%20I%20think%20those%20experiences%20eventually%20helped%20me%20succeed%20in%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20tiny%2C%20rural%20village%20in%20China.%20I%20didn't%20have%20electricity%20until%20I%20was%20in%20second%20grade.%20I%20was%20the%20only%20girl%20in%20my%20village%20who%20went%20to%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20last%20year%20of%20school%2C%20I%20read%20a%20story%20about%20a%20young%20woman%20with%20a%20similar%20background%20to%20mine%20who%20left%20her%20village%20for%20the%20big%20city%20in%20China%20to%20become%20a%20factory%20worker.%20She%20later%20started%20her%20own%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20moment%20changed%20my%20life.%20She%20unknowingly%20gave%20me%20permission%20to%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20left%20my%20village%20and%20went%20to%20Beijing.%20I%20started%20as%20a%20hotel%20maid%2C%20and%20later%20ran%20a%20small%20dry%20cleaning%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ad23f0ae-02d2-4075-9b1f-623df1c9673e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20immigrated%20to%20the%20US%20when%20I%20was%2026.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20speak%20much%20English%20at%20the%20time.%20My%20ex-husband%20wanted%20to%20come%20to%20the%20country%20for%20law%20school.%20I%20didn't%20really%20have%20a%20choice.%20I%20remember%20when%20I%20first%20got%20here%2C%20I%20turned%20on%20the%20TV%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20on%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20as%20I%20was%20learning%20English%2C%20I%20became%20inspired%20by%20Asian%20fashion%20designer%20Vera%20Wang.%20I%20applied%20to%20the%20Fashion%20Institute%20of%20Technology's%20fashion%20design%20program%2C%20but%20the%20major%20was%20very%20competitive.%20The%20school%20told%20me%20to%20wait%20another%20year%20and%20apply%20again.%20But%20I%20was%2028%20and%20I%20didn't%20feel%20like%20I%20had%20another%20year%20to%20wait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20applying%20to%20and%20being%20accepted%20to%20the%20home%20fashion%20and%20home%20textile%20surfaces%20major.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20my%20village%2C%20we%20planted%20and%20picked%20cotton%20and%20my%20grandma%20would%20put%20it%20into%20yarn%20on%20her%20big%2C%20wooden%20loom.%20We%20would%20bring%20the%20fabric%20to%20the%20market%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20inspired%20my%20love%20for%20textiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20graduated%2C%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20home%20fashion%20company%20for%20four%20years.%20But%20I%20always%20had%20that%20entrepreneurial%20dream%2C%20so%20after%20learning%20the%20business%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20could%20do%20better.%20I%20saw%20a%20blank%20space%20in%20the%20market%20for%20beautiful%20and%20stylish%20designs%20that%20were%20also%20accessible%20and%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f2d3d1d6-4671-4152-bec0-0b2a910c90ce%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lushdecor.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3ELush%20Decor%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20in%202008.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20the%20company%2C%20there%20were%20just%20a%20couple%20of%20people%20working%20with%20me.%20My%20job%20was%20focused%20mostly%20on%20design%20and%20product%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20working%2024%20hours%20a%20day%20at%20that%20time.%20I%20would%20design%20during%20the%20day%20and%20talk%20to%20the%20manufacturers%20at%20night%20because%20we%20had%20a%2012-hour%20time%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202008%20and%202009%2C%20all%20the%20big%20box%20retailers%20started%20freezing%20their%20buying%20because%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpositive-things-that-came-out-of-2008-recession-financial-crisis-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20any%20chances%20on%20new%20vendors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jenny%20Jing%20Zhu%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68193eb7c6ad288d14801538%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJenny%20Jing%20Zhu%20took%20inspiration%20from%20designer%20Vera%20Wang%20and%20her%20family's%20roots%20picking%20cotton.%3Cp%3EJenny%20Jing%20Zhu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20e-commerce%20was%20still%20new%20in%20the%20home%20fashion%20space.%20Everyone%20told%20me%20that%20I%20couldn't%20ship%20comforters%20or%20bedding%20to%20one%20customer%20at%20a%20time.%20They%20said%20it%20would%20be%20too%20expensive%20and%20people%20wouldn't%20buy%20our%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20really%20had%20no%20choice%2C%20because%20I%20couldn't%20do%20traditional%20business%20deals%20given%20the%20economic%20challenges%20and%20my%20own%20limited%20business%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20this%20very%20small%20warehouse%20behind%20our%20office%20and%20at%20the%20end%20of%20each%20day%2C%20I%20would%20go%20slap%20UPS%20and%20FedEx%20labels%20on%20the%20boxes%20one-by-one%20in%20my%20high%20heels.%20Not%20very%20many%20people%20were%20doing%20it%20that%20way%20in%20those%20days.%20There%20was%20no%20road%20map.%20I%20just%20learned%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20designs%20were%20unique%20in%20a%20boring%20market.%20Our%20first%20collection%20was%20inspired%20by%20Vera%20Wang%20wedding%20dresses.%20The%20bedding%20had%20hundreds%20of%20little%20bows%20on%20it%20and%20it%20sold%20out.%20I%20also%20used%20unique%20fabrics.%20I%20went%20back%20to%20China%20once%20and%20found%20crocodile%20skin.%20I%20put%20it%20on%20a%20bag%20and%20we%20sold%20so%20many%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20differentiated%20ourselves%20with%20unique%20designs%2C%20and%20that%20put%20us%20ahead%20in%20the%20e-commerce%20business.%20Very%20quickly%2C%20we%20became%20the%20major%20brand%20on%20the%20e-commerce%20market%2C%20selling%20millions%20of%20products%20to%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226074ab34-1faf-4807-9f23-eafbbf3f8354%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20was%20scary%20starting%20a%20business%20in%20that%20economic%20environment.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20that%20only%20a%20small%20percentage%20of%20businesses%20survive%20the%20first%20three%20years.%20I%20felt%20so%20much%20pressure%20in%20those%20early%20days%20because%20I%20was%20all%20on%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20built-in%20customer%20base%20when%20I%20started.%20No%20mentor%20or%20support%20community%20around%20me.%20I%20had%20no%20safety%20net%20to%20fall%20back%20on.%20I%20had%20such%20bad%20imposter%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20have%20an%20MBA%20or%20finance%20background%20but%20I'm%20very%20good%20at%20numbers.%20When%20I%20met%20with%20investors%2C%20I%20told%20them%2C%20I'm%20not%20only%20interested%20in%20designing%20beautiful%20products%3B%20I%20also%20design%20beautiful%20margins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20I%20had%20was%20passion%20and%20persistence%2C%20and%20that%20helped%20me%20build%20resilience%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20every%20point%20in%20my%20life%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20growing%20up%20in%20the%20village%20or%20being%20a%20hotel%20maid%20or%20nanny%20%E2%80%94%20I%20always%20found%20the%20creativity%20to%20make%20it%20work.%20I%20think%20that's%20in%20the%20DNA%20of%20entrepreneurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20scared%20to%20death%2C%20too%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20take%20that%20first%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22842fd9cd-5e57-4648-a74e-83e20daa5d78%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20first%20saw%20a%20profit%20in%202012.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20remember%20seeing%20that%20number%20going%20up%20and%20up.%20I%20just%20thought%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20god%2C%20that's%20the%20right%20direction!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20I%20partially%20sold%20to%20private%20equity.%20I%20stayed%20on%20as%20CEO%20for%20another%20three%20years%20and%20then%20as%20a%20board%20member.%20%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20company%20surpassed%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20in%20revenue%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20management%2C%20however%2C%20didn't%20end%20up%20working%20out%2C%20so%20I%20stepped%20back%20into%20the%20company%20fully%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20tariffs%20have%20hit%20a%20lot%20of%20businesses%20like%20ours%20really%20hard.%20Trying%20to%20%3Cem%3Estart%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20business%20at%20a%20time%20like%20this%20is%20even%20harder.%20The%202008%20economic%20crisis%20was%20like%201.0%3B%20the%20pandemic%20was%202.0%2C%20and%20these%20current%20times%20are%20like%203.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20source%20overseas%2C%20and%20this%20has%20definitely%20reminded%20entrepreneurs%20that%20we%20need%20to%20diversify%20our%20supply%20chains.%20But%20even%20so%2C%20there's%20not%20a%20lot%20you%20can%20do%20to%20diversify%20overnight.%20A%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20come%20from%20China%2C%20other%20countries%20can't%20do%20as%20efficiently.%20The%20tariffs%20are%20not%20just%20raising%20the%20prices%3B%20they're%20threatening%20an%20already%20fragile%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20business%20community%20is%20in%20really%20difficult%20situations%20right%20now.%20Times%20like%20these%20can%20force%20businesses%20to%20do%20something%20that%20they're%20likely%20lagging%20to%20do%2C%20which%20is%20diversifying%20their%20supply%20chains.%20Yes%2C%20it's%20very%20overwhelming%2C%20but%20you're%20not%20alone.%20We're%20all%20in%20the%20same%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntrepreneurs%20need%20to%20understand%20and%20accept%20what%20they%20can%20and%20can't%20control.%20Don't%20panic.%20Don't%20be%20angry%2C%20even%20though%20we%20are%20angry.%20Rely%20on%20your%20community%2C%20rely%20on%20your%20resources.%20Every%20time%20you%20go%20through%20things%20that%20could%20break%20you%2C%20you%20are%20building%20more%20resilience%20and%20confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-founded-startup-during-2008-financial-crisis-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747003501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68193e96a466d2b74ab518d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-founded-startup-during-2008-financial-crisis-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jenny%20Jing%20Zhu%20came%20to%20the%20US%20speaking%20little%20English.%20She%20started%20her%20now-%24100%20million%20home%20design%20company%20Lush%20Decor%20amid%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40businessinsider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-founded-startup-during-2008-financial-crisis-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bad%20Bunny%20and%20Fuerza%20Regida%20Make%20Chart%20History%20as%20Spanish-Language%20Albums%20Claim%20Top%20Spots%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747001110000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2F2-Split-3x2-1.jpg%3Fcrop%3D0px%252C13px%252C1000px%252C562px%26resize%3D1000%252C563%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fva