%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F190205%2Fladakh-world-sweetest-apricot-raktsey-karpo-drdo-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHalman%20apricots%20%E2%80%94%20touted%20to%20be%20the%20sweetest%20apricots%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20seabuckthorn%2C%20a%20shrub%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98wonder%20plant%E2%80%99%20for%20its%20various%20purposes.%20Both%20are%20prized%20in%20the%20global%20health-conscious%20market.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20there%20is%20entrepreneur%20Neha%20Upadhyaya%2C%20who%20has%20impacted%20over%203%2C000%20women%20in%20Ladakh%20through%20her%20platform%20%E2%80%98Guna%20Organics%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20integrates%20organic%20practices%20and%20solar%20technology%20in%20farming.%20As%20she%20shared%20in%20a%20previous%20interview%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20people%20of%20Ladakh%20were%20dependent%20on%20the%20apricot%3B%20rightly%20so%2C%20a%20major%20portion%20of%20the%20revenue%20is%20generated%20through%20its%20sale%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20But%20a%20little%20probing%20led%20her%20to%20discover%20that%20a%20kilo%20of%20apricots%20was%20retailing%20for%20just%20Rs%20150.%20Thus%20began%20Neha%E2%80%99s%20quest%20to%20educate%20them%20about%20sun%20drying.%20Currently%2C%20the%20fruit%20retails%20for%20Rs%20465.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Fguna-organics-9-1716443545-1746609141.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neha%20Upadhyay%20works%20closely%20with%20farmers%20in%20